The maven3 builder's log output in the "full build log" looks like:

{noformat}
simple	29-Feb-2012 01:31:53	Starting task 'Maven 3.x' of type 'com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.maven:task.builder.mvn3'
command	29-Feb-2012 01:31:53	Beginning to execute external process for build 'Nexus - Nexus OSS (master) - build'<br /> ... running command line: <br />/opt/apache-maven-3.0.3/bin/mvn<br />  -Djava.io.tmpdir=/tmp/NX-OSS-JOB1<br />  -V<br />  -e<br />  -B<br />  -Dmaven.repo.local=/mnt/bamboo-ebs/bamboo-agent/build-dir/NX-OSS-JOB1/repository<br />  -s<br />  build-config/maven/public-settings.xml<br />  clean<br />  verify<br />  -P<br />  zion-build, zion-capture-output<br />  -Dzion.outputRepository=/mnt/bamboo-ebs/bamboo-agent/build-dir/NX-OSS-JOB1/output<br /> ... in: /mnt/bamboo-ebs/bamboo-agent/build-dir/NX-OSS-JOB1<br /> ... using extra environment variables: <br />bamboo_maven_settings=build-config/maven/public-settings.xml<br />MAVEN2_HOME=/opt/apache-maven-3.0.3<br />JAVA_HOME=/mnt/bamboo-ebs/java/jdk1.6.0_31<br />useMavenReturnCode=<br />MAVEN_OPTS=-Xmx512m -XX:MaxPermSize=256m<br />M2_HOME=/opt/apache-maven-3.0.3<br />PATH=/mnt/bamboo-ebs/java/jdk1.6.0_31/bin:/opt/bamboo-elastic-agent/bin:/opt/jdk-6/bin:/opt/maven-2.1/bin:/opt/maven-1.0.2/bin:/opt/apache-ant-1.8.2/bin:/usr/local/bin:/bin:/usr/bin:/usr/local/sbin:/usr/sbin:/sbin:/opt/aws/bin:/home/bamboo/bin<br />
{noformat}

This is *very* hard to read and understand when looking at the plain/text log to see what was run.  The "full build log" should not include this markup and be easily readable by itself.

http://tardigrade.sydney.atlassian.com:8085/bamboo/browse/BAM-FC17-37 & http://tardigrade.sydney.atlassian.com:8085/bamboo/browse/BAM-FC17-36

A recent regression - FT please.
{noformat}
2012-02-28 22:11:09,120 ERROR [AtlassianEvent::0-BAM::EVENTS:pool-2-thread-14] [ChainExecutionManagerImpl] Failed to push for plan-result: BAM-FC17-37. RepositoryException during push: null
{noformat}

This should also log the exception type, I assume it's NPE? Is it possible to add NPE with a message for this case?
